 been placed in the ''Botrychium'' subgenus '''''Osmundopteris''''', the name of which is based on the species' superficial similarities to the genus ''Osmunda''<ref>Cobb, Farsworth & Lowe, ''Ferns of Northeastern North America'' 2nd edition, p. 247 (2005)</ref> where it was previously placed.\n* ''[[Botrychium virginianum]]'' {{au|(L.) Sw. 1801}}<ref>[http://www.tropicos.org/Name/26602189 ''B. virginianum''] Tropicos.org. Missouri Botanical Garden. 26 Dec 2011</ref> \u2013 Rattlesnake fern,<ref>{{PLANTS|id=BOVI|taxon=B. virginianum|accessdate=27 Dec 2011}}</ref> common grapefern<ref>[http://www.efloras.org/florataxon.aspx?flora_id=1&taxon_id=233500296 ''B. virginianum''] Flora of North America, www.eFloras.org 26 Dec 2011</ref><br>= ''[[Botrypus virginianus]]'' {{au|(L.) Michx. 1803}}\n\n===''Botrychium'' species placed in ''Sceptridium''===\n[[File:Botrychium rugulosum by OpenCage.jpg|thumb|right|''Botrychium rugulosum'']]\nThese species (the evergreen grapeferns) have traditionally been placed in the ''Botrychium'' subgenus '''''Sceptridium''''',a name based on the apparent similarity of their [[sporangia]] to \"little scepters.\"<ref>Cobb, Farsworth & Lowe, ''Ferns of Northeastern North America'' 2nd edition, p. 265 (2005)</ref>\n\n* ''[[Botrychium australe]]'' {{au|R.Br. 1810}}<ref>{{cite journal|last=Kelly|first=Dave|title=Demography and conservation of Botrychium australe, a peculiar, sparse mycorrhizal fern|journal=New Zealand Journal of Botany|year=1994|volume=32|issue=4|pages=393\u2013400|doi=10.1080/0028825x.1994.10412925}}</ref> \u2013 Parsley Fern<ref>[http://www.pfaf.org/user/Plant.aspx?LatinName=Botrychium+australe ''B. australe''] Plants for a Future 26 Dec 2011</ref>\n:= ''[[Sceptridium australe]]'' {{au|(R.Br.) Lyon 1905}}<ref>[http://www.ipni.org/ipni/idPlantNameSearch.do?id=228864-2 International Plant Names Index (IPNI) 17 Jan 2011]</ref>\n\n* ''[[Botrychium biforme]]'' {{au|Colenso 1886}}<ref>[http://www.ipni.org/ipni/idPlantNameSearch.do?id=17060960-1 ''B. biforme''] International Plant Names Index (IPNI) 02 Jan 2012</ref> \u2013 Fine-leaved parsley fern\n:= ''[[Sceptridium biforme]]'' {{au|(Colenso) Lyon 1905}}<ref>[http://www.ipni.org/ipni/idPlantNameSearch.do?id=17220050-1 ''S. biforme''] International Plant Names Index (IPNI) 02 Jan 2012</ref>\n\n* ''[[Botrychium biternatum]]'' {{au|(Savigny) Underw. 1896}} \u2013 Sparse-lobed grapefern, Southern grapefern<ref>[http://www.efloras.org/florataxon.aspx?flora_id=1&taxon_id=233500272 ''B. biternatum''] Flora of North America, www.eFloras.org 26 Dec 2011</ref>\n:= ''Osmunda biternata'' {{au|Savigny 1798}}\n:= ''[[Sceptridium biternatum]]'' {{au|(Savigny) Lyon 1905}}\n\n* ''[[Botrychium dissectum]]'' {{au|Sprengel 1804}}<ref>{{cite journal|last=Montgomery|first=James D.|title=Survivorship and Predation Changes in Five Populations of Botrychium dissectum in Eastern Pennsylvania|journal=American Fern Journal|year=1990|volume=80|issue=4|series=4|pages=173\u2013182|doi=10.2307/1547206|jstor=1547206}}</ref><ref>[http://www.tropicos.org/Name/26602173 ''B. dissectum''] Tropicos.org. Missouri Botanical Garden. 26 Dec 2011</ref> \u2013 Dissected grapefern<ref>[http://www.efloras.org/florataxon.aspx?flora_id=1&taxon_id=200002874 ''B. dissectum''] Flora of North America, www.eFloras.org 26 Dec 2011</ref> or Cut-leaved grape-fern<ref name=mich>[http://michiganflora.net/genus.aspx?id=Sceptridium] MICHIGAN FLORA ONLINE. A. A. Reznicek, E. G. Voss, & B. S. Walters. February 2011. University of Michigan. Web. January 16, 2012</ref>\n:= ''Botrychium obliquum'' {{au|Muhl. 1810}}<ref>[http://www.tropicos.org/Name/26604109?tab=acceptednames ''B. obliquum''] Tropicos.org. Missouri Botanical Garden. 16 Jan 2012</ref>\n:= ''[[Sceptridium dissectum]]'' {{au|(Spreng.) Lyon 1905}}\n\n* ''[[Botrychium jenmanii]]'' {{au|Underw. 1900}} \u2013 Alabama grapefern<ref>[http://www.efloras.org/florataxon.aspx?flora_id=1&taxon_id=233500279 ''B. jenmanii''] Flora of North America, www.eFloras.